  "body": "The `curl` call within the script *sometimes* (not always) throws an error:\r\n```\r\n# curl -sSLO https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubernetes/helm/master/scripts/get\r\n# chmod +x get\r\n# ./get\r\ncurl: (23) Failed writing body (0 != 1370)\r\nDownloading https://kubernetes-helm.storage.googleapis.com/helm-v2.5.1-linux-amd64.tar.gz\r\n```\r\nDue to curl writing to a pipe that is closed by `head -n 1` before all content is written:\r\n```\r\nTAG=$(curl -SsL $release_url | awk '/\\/tag\\//' | head -n 1 | cut -d '\"' -f 2 | awk '{n=split($NF,a,\"/\");print a[n]}')\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe curl maintainer [suggests to silence the error](http://thread.gmane.org/gmane.comp.web.curl.general/14941) due to the closing pipe with `curl -sL`, but this has the side effect of removing all error output.\r\n\r\nAnother suggestion of the `--no-buffer` option does not work.\r\nIgnoring the content length with `--ignore-content-length` does not work.",
